Full Outer Join 

	A FULL OUTER JOIN returns, All rows from the left table, All rows from the right table, 
	If there’s no match, NULLs appear in the columns of the table that doesn’t have a matching row.
	
	SELECT e.emp_id, e.emp_name, d.dept_name
	FROM employee e
	FULL OUTER JOIN department d
	ON e.dept_id = d.dept_id;
	
	--In Mysql Full Outer Join doesnot work so we use Union here 
	SELECT e.emp_id, e.emp_name, d.dept_name
	FROM employee e
	LEFT JOIN department d ON e.dept_id = d.dept_id
	UNION
	SELECT e.emp_id, e.emp_name, d.dept_name
	FROM employee e
	RIGHT JOIN department d ON e.dept_id = d.dept_id;